George J. Coates
 

 
 



GEORGE J. COATES is a research scientist in the design and development of power units and propulsion systems of numerous types, including gas turbines, steam turbines, pulse detonation, rocket engines, internal combustion engines and more. He is the inventor of the CSRV engine, the Coates Spherical Rotary Valve internal combustion engine, which is now believed to be the most advanced thermal efficient internal combustion engine in the world. George J. Coates is the founder, Chairman of the Board of Directors, and President and Chief Executive Officer of Coates International, Ltd. USA. His son, Gregory G. Coates, is Director and President, Technology Division. George J. Coates served two apprenticeships in Europe while attending the College of Technology in London and as an associate member of the Society of Automotive Engineers (S.A.E.) he received The City of Guilds of London for electrical and mechanical engineering. He is a former management director of SCR Motor Engineers of Europe. He worked as an engineer for Rolls Royce and Mercedes Benz, BLMC, Austin, and D. Napier. He holds approximately 300 patents worldwide on innovations and technologies, including the Coates Spherical Rotary Valve system and turbine engine, among others. He invented coolant disc brakes and a hydraulic suspension. He has delivered lectures and presentations at: TWTH Aachen University, Aachen, Germany, University of Birmingham, Birmingham, England and Rutgers University, New Brunswick, New Jersey, USA. He is a member of the Society of Mechanical Engineers and S.A.E. He received awards in 1995 for achievement in designs in automotive engineering from the S.A.E. He also received awards in 2001 for outstanding achievements in mechanical engineering from the American Society of Mechanical Engineers. Mr. Coates has extensive experience in international corporate business and has developed many long time associates and contacts in the business and scientific communities around the world.

 
 

Education
 
City and Guilds of London Institute. The College of Technology: Equivalence BE. BS. ME. EE. (Mechanical Engineering) (Electrical Engineering) (Physical Science) (Motor Engineering Certificate) – All With Honors. The American Society of Mechanical Engineers, Awarded for Outstanding Achievement in Mechanical Engineering, October 17, 2001. Awarded Associate Member S.A.E, The Engineering Society for Advancing Mobility Land Sea Air and Space International. (Licensed Inspector) The Presidential Business Commission. Chairman and Executive Committee Appointed George J.Coates to the Presidential Business Commission of the United States of America. Activities and Societies of The Job: Engineering Instructor ANCO The Industrial Training Authority. Amalgamated Engineering Union, London SE15, 5EL UK, B, L, M, C, R, R, Mercedes Benz. SCR Motor Engineers. Coates Engineering Ltd. Europe Design Engineering. Coates International, ltd. USA R&D. He is an accomplished musician. He plays piano and many other musical instruments as well as composes music.
 
 






Family



 George J. Coates and Bernadette Coates
