enerator set is the Cummins engine as it stands is not able to operate primetime or continuously.  They are only able to operate in emergency back-up operation.  Natural gas is not a good combustion engine fuel as it does not contain any lubricity; it is absolutely dry and poppet valve engines burn out with continuous operation.  On the other hand, the Coates CSRV green engine technology system will operate continuously with no adverse effects because of the CSRV rotation action, self-cleaning and lower temperature operation reduces wear and tear and also reduces fuel consumption and lowers the production of harmful emissions. The Cummins engine operating temperature averages 220° F.  The Coates CSRV operating temperature is 180° F.  This makes a big difference in the longevity of the power unit and a major reduction in harmful emissions produced such as CO, HC and NOX. There can be no assurance that the Company will be successful in any of its endeavors.Safe Harbor Statement: This press release contains forward-looking statements that are made pursuant to the safe harbor provisions of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995.  Please see our filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission.  Our public filings with the SEC may be viewed and printed on the website maintained by the SEC at http://www.sec.gov. Contact Information:Coates International, Ltd.Phone: 732-449-7717Fax: 732-449-0764www.coatesengine.comwww.mostadvancedengine.comWednesday - March 16, 2016COATES CSRV PATENTED GREEN ENGINE TECHNOLOGY BEING RETROFITTED TO AN 18 WHEELER HEAVY DUTY TRUCK AT THE COATES INTERNATIONAL, LTD. HEADQUARTERS IS UNDER WAY NOW -- HEAVY DIESEL TRUCKS CANNOT MEET THE NEW EMISSION WORLDWIDE STANDARDS -- AT COATES HEADQUARTERS THEY BELIEVE THEY HAVE THIS PROBLEM SOLVED -- PROJECT UPDATE PICTURES ARE POSTED ON THE COMPANY WEBSITE – WWW.COATESENGINE.COM Wall Township, NJ – (Marketwired – March 16, 2016): Coates International, Ltd. (OTC PINK: COTE) (the “Company”) has